The days of my youth were spent, like most of Qeynos's  residents, trying to rid the Hills of those wretched gnolls.  I, however, had a remarkably difficult time getting to Blackburrow from the city.  For some reason, the bears of Qeynos Hills took a shining to me.  Or shall I say, took a shining to chasing me.  I'd never even considered harming a bear as a young wizard in training, and certainly after meeting Merani, that trait would be reinforced.  yet, nonetheless, those bears would chase me down and maul me every chance they got until nearly a dozen seasons had passed.  Ask Merani next time you see her.  I'm sure she'll tell you how I spent a great deal of time running in my meager robe with a trail of one, two, or even three bears, on my tail.  She was forced to help me, of course, her loyalty to her God is second only to that of her friends.  So, she would distract them long enough for me to get to a new zone or to guards.  I know she hated to do it, and I owe much of my survival to her.  <br>
Soon there was talk of this warrior she met.  She spoke highly of him and when we met I could see why she was fond of him.  His name, if you hadn't already guessed, was Aydrian.  A fine bloke he was, I thought, and his knowledge of Norrath was leaps and bounds beyond anyone I'd known thus far.  And he was always there to lend a hand when needed.<br>
I can't count the times he and Merani bailed my fizzling little arse out of one of those Blackburrow pits.  I we them my life many times over, and that isn't even counting the journies to the Oasis that would soon follow.  How many times did a Sand Giant or a Spectre become the last thing I saw under those orange-green sunsets in that desert?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START >: --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/mad.gif ALT=">:"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
And those weeks spent in Highpass?  Many an orc died by my hand in those days, I'm proud to say.  Not    to say I didn't have my fair share of corpse runs through the Karanas.  <br>
Oh, the fear and excitement of those days growing, learning and...dying.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    But it was all worth it to meet all of those I would one day call fellow Arrows.<br>
Many faces have been and gone- including my own.  Phildefer, Mulk, Versukas, Cervania, the great Bangoo. And many old faces remain.  Jaron, the return of Montag, and Garomtel, who I met in those very early days of our guild's formation.  We grew to friends and adventured much together.  Then this Sytox fellow showed up.  I still wonder, where does he hide Gar, anyway?  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
